Well's Stores began as a village shop in 1834, but 20-30 yers ago it started specialising in{cheese.} It sells more than 150 kinds of cheese, including goats' and sheep's milk cheeses, French and English cheeses. The most popular cheese is{Farmhouse {Cheddar.}
Much of the{English cheese}comes from individual farms. Each farm has a different kind of soil which makes the grass different so that the cheese produced on that farm has its own distinctive taste.
People travel long distances to buy cheese here and the shop also sends cheese all over the world. Most goes to restaurants and hotels, and some to private mail-order customers.
